<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,332,359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamb, C. G." box="[346,493,333,359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="307 - 372" refId="ref16345" refString="Lamb, C. G. (1914) The Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905. XV. Diptera: Heteroneuridae, Ortalidae, Trypetidae, Sepsidae, Micropezidae, Drosophilidae, Geomyzidae, Milichilidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Series 2, Zoology, 16 (4), 307 - 372. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1913. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1914">Lamb (1914)</bibRefCitation>
provided a description of the species that was far ahead of its time in detail. It was based on a series of 
<specimenCount box="[377,485,368,395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="female">5 females</specimenCount>
that he reported had the head, palpi, thorax [scutum] and scutellum “orange”, and an arista with 3 dorsal branches (vs. the typical 2) plus the terminal fork. These features deviate from all continental Africa specimens, presumably why 
<bibRefCitation author="Burla, H." box="[548,690,440,467]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 218" refId="ref15506" refString="Burla, H. (1954) Zur kenntnis der Drosophiliden der Elfenbeinkuste (Franzosisch West-Afrika). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 61 (supplement), 1 - 218. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 75413" type="journal article" year="1954">Burla (1954)</bibRefCitation>
decided that 
<taxonomicName box="[836,895,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suma">
<emphasis box="[836,895,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">suma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represented a different species. Our examination of two specimens from the series reveals that Lamb erred only with the number of aristal branches, which have the typical 2 dorsal ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<materialsCitation collectingDate="1908-09" collectingDateMax="1908-11" collectingDateMin="1908-09" country="Seychelles" location="Seychelles" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" specimenCount="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Lamb, C. G." box="[199,345,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="307 - 372" refId="ref16345" refString="Lamb, C. G. (1914) The Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905. XV. Diptera: Heteroneuridae, Ortalidae, Trypetidae, Sepsidae, Micropezidae, Drosophilidae, Geomyzidae, Milichilidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Series 2, Zoology, 16 (4), 307 - 372. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1913. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1914">Lamb (1914)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned specimens from three localities in the 
<collectingCountry box="[897,1021,549,575]" name="Seychelles" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
: “Mahé, near Morne Blanc, 
<date box="[1334,1421,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-10">
<collectingDate box="[1334,1421,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-10">X.1908</collectingDate>
</date>
”, “Silhouette: Mare aux Cochons, 
<date box="[526,623,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-09">
<collectingDate box="[526,623,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-09">IX.1908</collectingDate>
</date>
”, and “Praslin: Côtes d’Or Estate, 
<date box="[1024,1122,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-11">
<collectingDate box="[1024,1122,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1908-11">XI.1908</collectingDate>
</date>
.” 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1209,585,611]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mahé</collectingCountry>
is the largest, main island; the other two are considerably smaller, Silhouette ~ 
<quantity box="[824,895,620,647]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="25.0">25 km</quantity>
NW and Praslin ~ 
<quantity box="[1105,1177,620,647]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="35.0">35 km</quantity>
NE of Mahé. For geographical coordinates see the Appendix table
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
In his identification of specimens from Natal, 
<collectingCountry box="[708,852,693,719]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas, L." box="[862,1016,693,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="103 - 161" refId="ref16778" refString="Tsacas, L. (1990) Drosophilidae de l'Afrique Australe (Diptera). Annals of the Natal Museum, 31, 103 - 161." type="journal article" year="1990">Tsacas (1990)</bibRefCitation>
did not indicate how he distinguished 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamb" authorityYear="1914" box="[151,278,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">
<emphasis box="[151,278,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">D. spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[347,441,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suma">
<emphasis box="[347,441,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">D. suma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and he later formally synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[856,950,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suma">
<emphasis box="[856,950,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">D. suma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tsacas, 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Tsacas" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[1029,1330,729,756]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">
<emphasis box="[1029,1156,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">D. spinipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas, L." box="[1171,1323,729,756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="49 - 58" refId="ref16805" refString="Tsacas, L. (2006) Nouvelles especes de la Cote D'Ivoire capturees au piege lumineux (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, 28 (2), 49 - 58." type="journal article" year="2006">Tsacas, 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. He must not have seen the NHMUK 
<typeStatus box="[468,516,765,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
series, which are immediately recognizable as distinct from the flies from 
<collectingCountry name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and continental Africa. Specimens in the Kwazulu-Natal Museum bear Tsacas’ identification labels, indicating that he dissected a male and female specimen from these (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas, L." box="[872,1024,837,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="103 - 161" refId="ref16778" refString="Tsacas, L. (1990) Drosophilidae de l'Afrique Australe (Diptera). Annals of the Natal Museum, 31, 103 - 161." type="journal article" year="1990">Tsacas, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Our study of these specimens and dissections and the undissected ones from Natal finds that they are 
<taxonomicName authority="Grimaldi &amp; Jones, 2020" authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Jones" authorityYear="2020" box="[903,1068,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalloserra" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[903,1068,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">D. phalloserra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1082,1135,873,899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
